text:
Manhattan Avenue, north from W. 113th Street. To the left is a triangular park at the convergence of this thoroughfare and Morningside Avenue, same begining here. The Monterey is the 7 story apartment house seen beyond same and nears No. 351 W. 114th Street. Note the gas lamps at the right and the electric fixture at the left.
June 1906.

Geo. L. Balgue

folder: Morningside Avenue & Manhattan Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
Morningside Park: Three views of the Harlem park. View 1 is southeastward from 116th Street and shows Morningside Avenue meeting Manhattan Avenue at 113th Street. View 2 shows the block on Morningside Avenue between 115th (right) and 116th Streets, and view 3 Manhattan Avenue at 112th Street.

View 1: April, 1906
View 2: February, 1920
View 3: July, 1928

Goerge L. Salgue
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE
